Wife of British hostage appeals for his return
The wife of Alan McMenemy, a British hostage still missing in Iraq, has made an emotional plea for his kidnappers to end his family's ordeal. Alan McMenemy (right) was protecting Peter Moore (left) when he was abducted in Iraq by gunmen 7:45AM BST 29 May 2010
Mr McMenemy, a security guard, was abducted three years ago by gunmen in Iraq along with three other guards and the IT expert they were protecting. His wife Rosaleen McMenemy urged those holding him to show "mercy and compassion" on Saturday, the anniversary of his abduction. Mr McMenemy is feared dead, but the kidnappers, an Iraqi Shia militia group, have yet to provide any proof. The bodies of the three other guards kidnapped at the same time have been returned to Britain while Peter Moore, the man they were protecting, was released alive in December last year. Mrs McMenemy said: "It's now been three years since he's been held captive, which is 1,096 days. Related Articles
Freed hostage Peter Moore tells of ordeal in Iraq
12 Mar 2010
